text: Prairie is an unincorporated community in Skagit County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Prairie was established in 1884, and remained in operation until 1925. The community took its name from a nearby prairie. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Skagit County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Prairie, Washington
